source "https://rubygems.org"

gem "github-pages", group: :jekyll_plugins
```

That's the standard one-liner for GitHub Pages. It tells GitHub's build system exactly which Jekyll version and plugins to use.

Then also add a `Gemfile.lock` to your `.gitignore` so it doesn't cause conflicts between your local machine and GitHub's build environment:
```
echo "Gemfile.lock" >> .gitignore
